I'd like to add on this one.

That's true, and we should always remind ourselves that *it's okay to see happiness as a good thing, but don't value happiness as a good thing* bcs then, you will start to chase it.

Having a friend like minghao feels like you can talk to him about anything (like anything).

author: @Koed313
text:
This episode was so nice. I would love to sit and have a chat with Minghao, they just feel so genuine and heartfelt. It would be right up my alley.

Having said that, I also wanted to say something unrelated here so don't mind me. I really, really loved the lightning during the third rounds in Dino, DK, Minghao and Joshua, Hoshi and Vernon's rooms. It was such a mood and even made their conversations seem so much cosier. And if and when I get my own place, that's what the setting I would want to be for my bedroom. I really really love those kind of lights, the dim but bright enough, yellow illumination with ac on and some peaceful quiet. I absolutely love bright lights but those (above-mentioned) are totally my vibe too.

author: @randomstuff3542
text: The last part got me teary-eyed. Felt like Minghao was talking to me. I think a lot of us can relate when it comes to wanting excellent results that we often miss out on the joy of the process itself and ignore other aspects of life.  As a design student, I always feel overwhelmed and easily burnt out because I tell myself I'm not good enough and I need to work harder. Thus, putting pressure on myself when designing to make it perfect. In the end, I don't enjoy the design process which is what I'm actually passionate about. I've had time to reflect on myself and it's like I'm just existing for the sake of existing and not actually living which is something I wanna change. So, Thank you Minghao for letting Hoshi hear what he and the rest of us needed to hear.

author: @annadang5811
text:
This episode is just such a gem. Too many of my fav moments!

Thirds with Seungkwan, Woozi, Jeonghan and Jun was so chaotic and funny, the "drinking way", calling NCT Jungwoo & doing Jun impressions, infinite karaoke with Cheol, Gyu and Wonwoo, funny and deep convo with Dino, DK and Minghao and of course Vernon, Shut and Hoshi talking about movies.

The car rides were also fun to watch, Gyu and Vernon just taking naps they deserve, and especially Minghao and Hoshi's talk about happiness, resting/relaxing and work-life-balance. 

I think I will need to rewatch this at some point again. ğŸ’

author: @dotdotdot...176
text:
- it's so hilarious how they seem tipsy/act drunk after drinking just water or the non-alcoholic versions of drinks 
- I love how playful and active Woozi was in this episode, really cute, endearing and entertaining
- 3D team (Dino, DK and "Dee8") is so funny
- Mingyu, Wonwoo and Coups are literally the rappers yet big ballad fans so it was perfect for them to end up together 
- Vernon going to see an animated movie but there's mostly little kids is very relatable
- Josh being shocked at a fan being born in 2007 is also very relatable; I'm still young but that makes me feel old lol
- I enjoyed all the skits from DK and Dino to Jeonghan and Woozi, I love that in this universe Woozi has a daughter Iseul lol
- The Jun impressions were hilarious, especially when he impersonated himself and the call with Jungwoo seemed really wholesome and cute 
- Minghao and Hoshi's heart to heart really touched me... I too am trying to find happiness in the simple things 
- to be honest it's kinda sad that Dino doesn't know the standard for his age, since he's been in the spotlight as an idol since so young he doesn't experience what the average person his age feels like

Minghao, you are so right - chasing our personal happiness means so much, even if it's found in the stillness of time. I've learned that from making sense of reality over these past two years. Like Wonwoo, I also don't feel my age yet - I will be 25 next month, but it feels like I'm still 21/22. But maybe age isn't something to focus on, but personal growth. No matter the position or career in life, we must find that internal joy to be truly fulfilled. Thank you Seventeen for being true to yourself in this world of make-believe and pretentiousness. My heart and mind feel right after watching your content and listening to your music. You did amazing yesterday - the last day of your NA tour, and I want to say that I am proud of you and admire your hard work and humility which is constant no matter where you go! Keep changing the world of music and continue being who you are! We love you!

author: @devlinadas3686
text:
I conencted with Dino and Wonwoo the most, because first of all I am the same age as Dino and I am the younger sibling, I just got a job and today I finished my first month at work and got my payment and believe me, I realized that I need to grow up now, I still myself as a 17 year old just like Dino said...but somehow, time has always been flying for me, my 15 years of school seemed to finish in a jiffy, so did my college, and now I am working...
Guys, try to live like Minghao as you grow up...I also agree with the others that the ones born after 2001 seem so odd to someone who was lucky to be born at the last moment of the 20th century...being a teacher it was really odd for me on the first day that the children were born 4-5 years after I was born...
I am older now, now is the time for our generation to work for us and for the ear future for the next genration....

author: @i1woo
text:
*different aspects of seventeen in this episode:*


*joshua, vernon* and *hoshi* talking about latest korean dramas and movies they've recently watched. _that's seventeen sharing common interests._

*wonwoo, scoups* and *mingyu* singing, recommending songs and talking about doing covers. _that's seventeen being talented artists._

*dk, dino, jeonghan* and *woozi* instinctively doing skits like they usually do, filming a trailer that would arouse interests for viewers. _that's seventeen being effortlessly witty entertainers._

*jun* and *seungkwan* calling and catching up with their friend, showing us their interpersonal interactions outside of their group. _that's seventeen being wholesome and friendly._

*minghao* talking about the pressures of their work, reminding them of finding happiness in simple things, and the importance of one's mental health. _that's seventeen caring for each other like family._

author: @karitthasun290
text:
I have to give it up to the Going Staff team. At first, I thought the concept of a company dinner with no alcohol, filmed in the middle of the day would be the most awkward content ever produced. There were some moments that I went "Eek... this could be more awkward than the Carnival". But after finishing both episodes, I was like this is so raw and so nice. I got to see new sides to the members and even get to hear behind-the-scenes, the everyday life of Seventeen when they meet up with each other. I get to see: 
-  different expressions of Wonwoo in this episode
- the cute 3-poses from Jun
- the raw and caring side of The8
- the humble and reflective side of Hoshi as he listens to The8 even though he's the older one
- the easily drunk-on atmosphere Mingyu
- the skit-lovers Jeonghan and Woozi
- Seungkwan and his friendship with NCT
- Dino and his growing confidence and cheerfulness
- Joshua and his preference for movies over dramas
- the favorite playlist of Scoups - Tattoo
- Vernon and his insights into movies especially on Inception - I'm going to watch it to see the ring 
- of course, how much I would love to have drinks with DK - mood maker, deep listener, empathizer, reliable friend. I have got a whole POV of what can happen when we drink together LOL

author: @RinRin_1223
text: That talk with Minghao and Hoshi makes me emotional. It's true, Hoshi and all SVT members have worked so hard ever since their trainee days, they deserve all the recognition. The way Minghao reminded Hoshi that it's okay to rest and take a break to recharged himself is so precious. I do notice that whenever it's the two of them there's always that gentle warm feeling (not saying that you can't see that on other members), like on their In the Soop episode where Hoshi asked Minghao to explain the book he's reading, it's just so precious. Their friendship is so valuable. We all need a friend like Hoshi who encourages us to always work hard and Minghao who reminds us that it's okay to rest as well.
